  "hypothesis": "The prior 2.0 traction recovery hip scale crosses a sagittal pitch-divergence boundary during severe slip. Latching severity from a signed 0.15 rad backward-pitch excursion, then bounding only the severe response at 1.74, should preserve mild-slip traction authority while preventing backward tumble without phase-sensitive velocity classification.",
  "expectedEffect": "Eliminate all ten extreme-traction baseline violations, retain every completed regression gate, and keep friction 0.05 as honest non-gating stress evidence."
